## Tables & Views

### Create table — correct pattern for Rocket projects
```sql
CREATE TABLE orders (
  id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  status      order_status DEFAULT 'pending',   -- enum (see below)
  amount      INTEGER NOT NULL,                  -- always store money in cents
  metadata    JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  deleted_at  TIMESTAMPTZ                        -- soft delete (NULL = not deleted)
);

ALTER TABLE orders ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE INDEX orders_user_id_idx ON orders(user_id);       -- index every FK
CREATE INDEX orders_status_idx ON orders(status);         -- index every filtered column
CREATE INDEX orders_created_at_idx ON orders(created_at); -- index sort columns
```

### Views — always set security_invoker = true
```sql
-- security_invoker = true means RLS from underlying table applies through the view
-- security_invoker = false (default!) means view owner's permissions used — bypasses RLS
CREATE VIEW active_orders
WITH (security_invoker = true) AS
SELECT * FROM orders WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
```

### Materialized views (for expensive aggregations)
```sql
CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW monthly_revenue AS
SELECT
  DATE_TRUNC('month', created_at) AS month,
  SUM(amount) AS total_cents
FROM orders
WHERE status = 'completed'
GROUP BY 1;

-- Refresh manually or via pg_cron
REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW CONCURRENTLY monthly_revenue;
```

### Soft delete pattern (recommended over hard deletes)
```typescript
// Delete = set deleted_at, never actually remove the row
const { error } = await supabase
  .from('orders')
  .update({ deleted_at: new Date().toISOString() })
  .eq('id', orderId)

// Always filter out soft-deleted rows in queries
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('orders')
  .select()
  .is('deleted_at', null)   // .is() for NULL comparisons — not .eq()
```

### Upsert
```typescript
// Insert if not exists, update if exists (based on unique constraint)
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('profiles')
  .upsert({ id: user.id, username: 'alice' }, { onConflict: 'id' })
  .select()
  .single()
```

