## Enums

```sql
-- Create enum type
CREATE TYPE order_status AS ENUM ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'cancelled', 'refunded');

-- Use in table
CREATE TABLE orders (
  status order_status DEFAULT 'pending'
);

-- Add a new value to existing enum (append only — cannot remove/reorder)
ALTER TYPE order_status ADD VALUE 'on_hold' AFTER 'processing';

-- List all enum values
SELECT unnest(enum_range(NULL::order_status));
```

```typescript
// TypeScript — define matching type (or use generated types from supabase gen types)
type OrderStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'

// Query with enum filter
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('orders')
  .select()
  .in('status', ['pending', 'processing'])
```

